OL,3,CStarmer to reassure public as Iran
OL,4,Cconflict enters tenth day
OL,6,FSir Keir Starmer will seek to reassure
OL,7,Fthe public at home as the Middle East
OL,8,Fconflict continues into its tenth day.
OL,10,FThe Prime Minister will discuss the
OL,11,Fimpact on people in the UK as he
OL,12,Fvisits a London community centre on
OL,13,FMonday.
OL,15,FAhead of the visit he said the UK is
OL,16,F"working round the clock to keep
OL,17,FBritish citizens safe" and
OL,18,Facknowledged that Britons at home are
OL,19,F"worried sick" for friends and family.
OL,26,@xD@AOUyD@VO]{D@AOU{D@NO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773034803
OL,3,CStarmer to reassure public as Iran
OL,4,Cconflict enters tenth day
OL,6,F"Staff are on the ground to support
OL,7,Fthose in need, government-provided
OL,8,Fflights are helping people get home,
OL,9,Fand our tireless armed forces are
OL,10,Fflying across the region to defend our
OL,11,Fallies and our interests," he said.
OL,13,FIt comes amid speculation over the
OL,14,Fimpact of the war on the global
OL,15,Feconomy.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
